f_X(x)={{r+x-1} \choose x} p^r (1-p)^x ,x=0,1,2,\ldots, 0<p<1,\mbox{ and }r\in\mathbb{Z}^+
M_X(t)
e^{xt}
\sum_{x=0}^\infty e^{xt}{{r+x-1} \choose x} p^r (1-p)^x
e^{e^t(1-p)}
p^r\sum_{x=0}^\infty \frac{(r+x-1)!}{(r-1)!}\boxed{\frac{(e^t(1-p))^x}{x!}}
(1)
q=1-p
 M_X(t)=p^r\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\binom{r+n-1}{n}(e^t(1-p))^n=p^r(1-(1-p)e^t)^{-r}=\left(\frac{p}{1-(1-p)e^t}\right)^r. 
 M_X(t)=\left(\frac{p}{1-qe^t}\right)^r. 
